Bracket in tweet below!â€¦ https://t.co/cInlpTWvvr

Final set of 10 characters! Starting off with a double image for Steve. Very common character, but Acola has a much wider lead than last time, and just over 20% of all results. Marth has seen some steady improvement, with two solo mains and a lot of use from Rizeasu. https://t.co/nxNMKsAvxF

Next up - Joker. Tsubaki has dethroned Leo in terms of Joker contributions this season. Not surprising between attendance and Leo's varied character pool. Toon Link is another Japan sweep with the top 3, but NA puts up respectable results too. https://t.co/LjjWf9Sli2

Min Min is a bit crazy with Proto's absence. Unsurprisingly, she's a Japan-centric character, which is a carry over from her popularity during Quarantine. Skyjay is the undisputed KING of Incineroar, sporting nearly 75% of the character's results. https://t.co/6whP3DL3mr

Luigi is a mess of a lot of competing top players, with Yamanaction narrowly at 1st during the season - though it's hard to parse instances of when he used Luigi more as a secondary. Olimar remains a low-use character with dedicated & successful mains. https://t.co/iumIAG1eGG

Lastly, Sephiroth & Richter: Sephiroth is a widely used co-main/secondary, but Sriks and M4E probably the most successful mostly-solo players. Richter struggled a lot this season, declining, but T3 DOM and TRIGGER are still his biggest mains. https://t.co/oufyX1qEbx
